{"word":"Ῥωμαῖος","slug":"Ῥωμαῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ῥωμαῖος, α, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ῥώμη\">Ῥώμη</a></el>] <b>Roman,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ funct.\">funct.</a> as noun<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> specifically of imperial Roman authorities, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pl.\">pl.</a> <b><a href='B:500 11:48'>J 11:48</a>; <a href='B:510 25:16'>Ac 25:16</a>; <a href='B:510 28:17'>28:17</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> sense of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> having right of citizenship in imperial Rome <b><a href='B:510 2:10'>Ac 2:10</a>; <a href='B:510 16:21'>16:21</a>, <a href='B:510 16:37'>37f</a>; <a href='B:510 22:25-27'>22:25-27</a>, <a href='B:510 22:29'>29</a>; <a href='B:510 23:27'>23:27</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ῥωμαϊκός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Ῥωμαϊστί\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}